{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/blog/be-careful-with-simple-components","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Be careful with \"simple\" examples. Especially with some solutions that look too good to be true.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; flex:0.9588235294117647;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/04cde12607105165153b307b8721fddc/ee455/simple-menu-component.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 104.29447852760735%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"component demo\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/04cde12607105165153b307b8721fddc/a6d36/simple-menu-component.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/04cde12607105165153b307b8721fddc/222b7/simple-menu-component.png 163w,\n/static/04cde12607105165153b307b8721fddc/ff46a/simple-menu-component.png 325w,\n/static/04cde12607105165153b307b8721fddc/a6d36/simple-menu-component.png 650w,\n/static/04cde12607105165153b307b8721fddc/ee455/simple-menu-component.png 863w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Developers call it \"simple\", but simplified API does not always mean small and clean code under the hood.</p>\n<h2 id=\"a-simple-sliding-side-menu-component-for-react\" style=\"position:relative;\">A simple sliding side menu component for React<a href=\"#a-simple-sliding-side-menu-component-for-react\" aria-label=\"a simple sliding side menu component for react permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; flex:1.2538461538461538;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0af62b3495289ba60740d75dfcdd18d0/f87c7/simple-menu-code.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 79.75460122699387%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"component code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/0af62b3495289ba60740d75dfcdd18d0/a6d36/simple-menu-code.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0af62b3495289ba60740d75dfcdd18d0/222b7/simple-menu-code.png 163w,\n/static/0af62b3495289ba60740d75dfcdd18d0/ff46a/simple-menu-code.png 325w,\n/static/0af62b3495289ba60740d75dfcdd18d0/a6d36/simple-menu-code.png 650w,\n/static/0af62b3495289ba60740d75dfcdd18d0/e548f/simple-menu-code.png 975w,\n/static/0af62b3495289ba60740d75dfcdd18d0/f87c7/simple-menu-code.png 1247w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>I don't need swipe, but the Cheeseburger component implements only that.</li>\n<li>Burger icon that doesn't look pretty with default props, come on, there are only 3 divs, what can be simpler?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>My point here, it's a good example for reference, but it can be much much simpler to be called \"simple\".</p>\n<h2 id=\"good-abstractions-and-evil-code\" style=\"position:relative;\">Good abstractions and evil code<a href=\"#good-abstractions-and-evil-code\" aria-label=\"good abstractions and evil code permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>On the other hand, often we need all these abstractions to be free from boilerplate code and do only things that we paid for - write business logic.</p>\n<p>It sounds paranoid, but you need to know what's inside every library before you can trust them.</p>\n<p>Here is the beauty of Open Source: you can check sources of any library and learn something new.</p>\n<p>I look at such tidbits and soak in the collective intelligence. 3 examples:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>How good that design pattern does fit into this problem, right?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This is how I found the \"trick\" used in Qt libraries that allows one to update Qt shared objects/DLLs without linking the app again.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>What is a clean approach of component/module/code organization?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Keep the root folder clean, use separate folder for build.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Wait, this statement shouldn't work in this language... 🤯</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Almost anything from Code Golf.</p>\n<p>No article can teach you better than a working code.</p>","excerpt":"Be careful with \"simple\" examples. Especially with some solutions that look too good to be true.  Developers call it \"simple\", but…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a-simple-sliding-side-menu-component-for-react\">A simple sliding side menu component for React</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#good-abstractions-and-evil-code\">Good abstractions and evil code</a></li>\n</ul>","fields":{"socialcard":"gatsby-plugin-social-card/2c490dc3-4c16-583c-8574-5587fecad2d7.jpg"},"frontmatter":{"date":"July 15, 2021","published":"October 14, 2021","lastModified":"October 14, 2021","title":"Be careful with \"simple\" components","subtitle":null,"section":null,"draft":null,"developing":null,"buttonText":null,"buttonLink":null,"secondButtonText":null,"secondButtonLink":null,"featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"showLikes":true,"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/blog/be-careful-with-simple-components.md","url":"/blog/be-careful-with-simple-components","next":{"excerpt":"I found so many questions on StackOverflow without answer regarding this problem: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/47973666/how-to-center…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/blog/center-window-in-weston.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Center window in Weston","date":"2021-07-24T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"05cdf99c-26f6-5104-99ba-c1099c1e5063"},"previous":{"excerpt":"What is the best navigation option for a website on mobile device? Hamburger menu Tap bar Bottom navigation Sli